[China Fire and Rescue]

50
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:23,620
[Detachment Leader's Office]

51
00:05:27,740 --> 00:05:28,260
Sir.

52
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:28,860
Come in.

53
00:05:35,670 --> 00:05:38,300
You put out the fire in Wufang Street

54
00:05:38,740 --> 00:05:39,700
and got the credit.

55
00:05:45,230 --> 00:05:46,460
This tea is of top quality.

56
00:05:46,460 --> 00:05:47,460
I didn't see it last time.

57
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:48,250
Put it down.

58
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:52,010
Come here.

59
00:05:56,470 --> 00:05:57,610
Not only the tea

60
00:05:58,210 --> 00:05:59,520
but also the credit and commendation,

61
00:05:59,540 --> 00:06:00,550
put them aside.

62
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:04,440
I just received three complaints.

63
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,960
Three complaints.

64
00:06:07,630 --> 00:06:08,310
First,

65
00:06:08,420 --> 00:06:10,630
our partner department complained that you

66
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:12,750
didn't cooperate with them

67
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:14,990
and acted rudely.

68
00:06:15,010 --> 00:06:15,730
Second,

69
00:06:15,910 --> 00:06:17,790
the public complained that you

70
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:18,860
have a bad attitude

71
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,190
and you ruined their

72
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:20,960
car.

73
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:23,020
Third,

74
00:06:23,020 --> 00:06:24,540
your colleagues complained that you

75
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,870
disobeyed the commander's order.

76
00:06:28,060 --> 00:06:28,660
No cooperation,

77
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:29,380
bad attitude,

78
00:06:29,380 --> 00:06:30,100
and disobedience.

79
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:30,620
You...

80
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:31,220
You...

81
00:06:31,420 --> 00:06:32,659
S-Shouldn't you...

82
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:33,540
Shouldn't you

83
00:06:33,540 --> 00:06:35,220
explain to me?

84
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:37,850
The car was supposed to be flipped over.

85
00:06:38,140 --> 00:06:38,900
They deserved the beating.

86
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:40,510
Since they were incompetent, they were supposed to be scolded.

87
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:42,790
If I annoy you,

88
00:06:43,010 --> 00:06:44,210
just transfer me away.

89
00:06:47,420 --> 00:06:49,040
Do you think I dare not?

90
00:06:49,380 --> 00:06:51,900
You always make trouble for me.

91
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:53,440
Every month,

92
00:06:54,060 --> 00:06:54,980
not even for a moment you are behaving yourself.

93
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:55,909
Mr. Gao.

94
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:57,850
Tell me.

95
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:00,010
Mr. Gao.

96
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:00,870
Calm down.

97
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:02,830
I got some information.

98
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:03,940
It was because the fire

99
00:07:03,970 --> 00:07:04,960
was raging dangerously.

100
00:07:05,220 --> 00:07:06,340
Song Yan

101
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:08,230
and the comrades at Wufang Street Fire Station

102
00:07:08,260 --> 00:07:09,170
had a few disagreements

103
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:10,520
about the way to deal with the fire.

104
00:07:10,850 --> 00:07:11,420
Later,

105
00:07:11,420 --> 00:07:12,820
they carried out Song Yan's plan

106
00:07:12,820 --> 00:07:14,580
and prevented the fire from spreading.

107
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:17,500
As for the car flipping,

108
00:07:17,780 --> 00:07:19,580
they couldn't reach the owner

109
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:21,300
of the private car which occupied the fire exit,

110
00:07:22,060 --> 00:07:23,100
so Song Yan did it that way

111
00:07:23,290 --> 00:07:24,930
to get to the fire scene as soon as possible

112
00:07:24,930 --> 00:07:26,460
and reduce the loss of lives and property

113
00:07:26,460 --> 00:07:27,820
of people, right?

114
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:32,170
You always get to find excuses

115
00:07:32,210 --> 00:07:33,210
to cover for him.

116
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:34,420
Mr. Gao,

117
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,690
you always say

118
00:07:35,710 --> 00:07:36,950
a fire scene is like a battlefield.

119
00:07:37,380 --> 00:07:38,340
We always face complex situations

120
00:07:38,370 --> 00:07:39,930
as we work at the frontline.

121
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:41,210
It's hard to

122
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:42,580
be well-considered in every aspect.

123
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:45,300
If Song Yan didn't

124
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:47,220
insist on bringing the squad in,

125
00:07:47,980 --> 00:07:49,940
the little boy and girl

126
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:51,620
wouldn't have been rescued.

127
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:55,300
Fine.

128
00:07:55,740 --> 00:07:57,260
I won't pursue the other two matters.

129
00:07:58,500 --> 00:07:59,980
But you have flipped over the car.

130
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:01,780
It is of so many negative influences.

131
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:02,860
We have to deal with it.

132
00:08:03,060 --> 00:08:03,460
That's right.

133
00:08:03,740 --> 00:08:04,660
Ask him to write a report.

134
00:08:05,140 --> 00:08:06,420
I submitted it last time.

135
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:07,380
Why do I still have to write?

136
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:09,420
That means it wasn't detailed enough last time.

137
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:10,340
Write it.

138
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:11,900
Write it.

139
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:13,140
3,000 words.

140
00:08:14,820 --> 00:08:16,320
Not even a word less.

141
00:08:16,540 --> 00:08:17,540
If missing one word,

142
00:08:18,660 --> 00:08:19,740
you'll be punished for an extra thousand.

143
00:08:26,060 --> 00:08:26,820
Song Yan.

144
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:30,620
Song Yan.

145
00:08:34,809 --> 00:08:35,740
I heard that

146
00:08:35,740 --> 00:08:37,100
the gas tank at the scene exploded.

147
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:37,980
It was very dangerous.

148
00:08:39,130 --> 00:08:40,299
I'm not blaming you.

149
00:08:40,530 --> 00:08:41,740
But can you stop

150
00:08:41,740 --> 00:08:43,130
rushing forward every time?

151
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,100
Saving people is important,

152
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,460
but also your safety.

153
00:08:46,820 --> 00:08:47,460
Now when I hear

154
00:08:47,460 --> 00:08:48,370
you go on a mission,

155
00:08:48,370 --> 00:08:49,540
I feel worried and anxious.

156
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:52,740
Thank you for your concern, madam.

157
00:08:53,060 --> 00:08:53,940
I'll take my leave first.

158
00:08:54,220 --> 00:08:54,860
I...

159
00:09:04,220 --> 00:09:05,610
Dr. Xu Qin who just came here

160
00:09:05,610 --> 00:09:06,890
is fabulous.

161
00:09:07,180 --> 00:09:08,700
I heard she'll be given the chance

162
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:10,020
to join the scientific research team.

163
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:10,860
Why is she?

164
00:09:11,140 --> 00:09:12,740
Just because she studied in the USA before?

165
00:09:12,910 --> 00:09:14,500
She's only been here for a while.

166
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:15,700
Is she experienced enough?

167
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:18,580
That's why they sent her to the ER.

168
00:09:18,740 --> 00:09:19,490
It may seem unjustifiable

169
00:09:19,490 --> 00:09:20,500
for her to join the scientific research team

170
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:22,580
after a period.

171
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:23,460
But

172
00:09:23,540 --> 00:09:24,740
you can't find fault with it.

173
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:26,500
They'll say it's an exception.

174
00:09:26,620 --> 00:09:27,860
I think

175
00:09:28,020 --> 00:09:29,020
it should be your turn

176
00:09:29,020 --> 00:09:30,300
to get the opportunity.

177
00:09:30,850 --> 00:09:31,940
You're older

178
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:32,940
and more experienced than her.

179
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:34,060
But you have no choice.

180
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:35,420
She has a backer.

181
00:09:36,460 --> 00:09:37,860
If that is how it works,

182
00:09:37,860 --> 00:09:38,780
we should all find ourselves a backer.

183
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:40,500
Everyone has connections and family backgrounds.

184
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:42,900
Her family background is extraordinary.

185
00:09:43,340 --> 00:09:44,930
I heard that her surname is Meng.

186
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:46,060
She changed her surname

187
00:09:46,060 --> 00:09:47,020
because she wanted to keep it low-profile.

188
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:49,020
Her surname is Meng?

189
00:09:49,020 --> 00:09:49,770
Meng what?

190
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:51,540
The Guokun Group.

191
00:09:51,540 --> 00:09:52,660
Really?

192
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:54,220
Her father is Meng Huaijin?

193
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:55,620
It's written in the file.

194
00:09:55,780 --> 00:09:57,220
When I helped her with the employee orientation,

195
00:09:57,220 --> 00:09:58,220
I saw it with my own eyes.

196
00:09:59,180 --> 00:10:00,300
So the one who comes to the hospital every day

197
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:01,300
to pick her up from work,

198
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,060
who is also handsome

199
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:03,260
and noble,

200
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:05,620
is the young master of the Guokun Group.

201
00:10:05,860 --> 00:10:07,340
He picks her up every day,

202
00:10:07,340 --> 00:10:08,660
not even a day is missing.

203
00:10:09,220 --> 00:10:10,370
When I think about the fact that

204
00:10:10,370 --> 00:10:11,180
I will be working with

205
00:10:11,180 --> 00:10:12,140
someone who was hired because of her connections,

206
00:10:12,460 --> 00:10:13,500
I feel jinxed.

207
00:10:22,530 --> 00:10:23,260
If you don't want to

208
00:10:23,260 --> 00:10:24,140
work with me,

209
00:10:24,850 --> 00:10:25,580
I can help you to

210
00:10:25,580 --> 00:10:26,500
deliver the message to the superior.

211
00:10:28,860 --> 00:10:29,660
Do you need it?

212
00:10:47,510 --> 00:10:49,270
[Emergency]

213
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:53,560
Brother.

214
00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,300
You got a new car?

215
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:02,210
[Emergency]

216
00:11:00,940 --> 00:11:01,940
It's your new car.

217
00:11:02,580 --> 00:11:03,500
I picked it for you.

218
00:11:03,780 --> 00:11:04,540
How is it?

219
00:11:04,580 --> 00:11:05,340
Do you like it?

220
00:11:05,430 --> 00:11:09,490
[Emergency]

221
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,820
Your taste is getting better.

222
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:09,380
What else can I do?

223
00:11:09,740 --> 00:11:10,780
You don't want to go home,

224
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:12,260
nor allow the driver to pick you up.

225
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:14,250
Mum is worried that you'd face difficulties in commuting.

226
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:16,300
Try it.

227
00:11:16,370 --> 00:11:17,380
If it doesn't suit you,

228
00:11:17,380 --> 00:11:18,340
I'll change to another one for you.

229
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:22,100
Thanks.

230
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:32,250
[Emergency]

231
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:52,020
The tunnel ahead is blocked because of an accident.

232
00:11:52,020 --> 00:11:53,300
Please make a detour.

233
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:54,980
Okay. Is anyone hurt?

234
00:11:55,660 --> 00:11:56,900
The car was wrecked.

235
00:11:57,020 --> 00:11:58,700
The person must be badly injured.

236
00:11:58,940 --> 00:11:59,980
The ambulance will be here soon.

237
00:11:59,980 --> 00:12:01,180
Don't block the way.

238
00:12:01,180 --> 00:12:01,770
Okay.

239
00:12:01,770 --> 00:12:02,610
Thank you for your cooperation.

240
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:14,220
You're already off from work.

241
00:12:14,770 --> 00:12:16,050
But I'm still a doctor.

242
00:12:17,530 --> 00:12:19,010
The ambulance will be here soon.

243
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:20,740
One more minute wasted,

244
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:21,980
the more dangerous the victim is.

245
00:12:21,980 --> 00:12:22,770
Brother.

246
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:25,530
Take care.

247
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,870
[Police]

248
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:36,860
Hello.

249
00:12:37,090 --> 00:12:37,860
I'm a doctor.

250
00:12:37,860 --> 00:12:39,060
Do you need help?

251
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:45,460
A doctor is volunteering to help.

252
00:12:45,540 --> 00:12:46,780
Should we let her in?

253
00:12:47,090 --> 00:12:47,930
Let her in.

254
00:12:48,490 --> 00:12:49,200
Okay.

255
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,620
Follow me.

256
00:13:10,190 --> 00:13:13,690
[Emergency]

257
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:17,620
The ambulance is here.

258
00:13:18,950 --> 00:13:19,630
Hence,

259
00:13:19,660 --> 00:13:21,100
we won't waste your time anymore.

260
00:13:21,630 --> 00:13:22,430
It's okay.

261
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:23,360
Thank you.

262
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:50,600
[Rescue]

263
00:14:07,340 --> 00:14:11,370
[Rescue]

264
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:26,300
Let's go.

265
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:37,940
Go.

266
00:15:14,380 --> 00:15:15,260
Supervisor.

267
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:16,540
Is the Deputy Chief not here?

268
00:15:17,340 --> 00:15:17,980
No, he's not.

269
00:15:18,140 --> 00:15:18,900
He's on duty.

270
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:21,210
Thank you for your hard work.

271
00:15:21,380 --> 00:15:22,530
Come and have a bite.

272
00:15:22,970 --> 00:15:23,810
Five minutes.

273
00:15:24,350 --> 00:15:25,620
Take your turns to eat.

274
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,610
You can't eat because of the toothache.

275
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:35,970
Have some soup.

276
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:46,190
How are you?

277
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,410
Are you feeling better?

278
00:15:59,650 --> 00:16:00,770
I'll go back later.

279
00:16:00,930 --> 00:16:01,970
Why did you come?

280
00:16:02,140 --> 00:16:02,580
I just

281
00:16:02,580 --> 00:16:03,460
want you to finish the meal early

282
00:16:03,460 --> 00:16:04,460
and go home early.

283
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,290
[Yuanyuan]

284
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:21,980
[Fire]

285
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:21,880
Hello.

286
00:16:23,210 --> 00:16:23,850
Yes, I have eaten.

287
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:25,880
We have a mission today.

288
00:16:30,310 --> 00:16:31,100
I know.

289
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:32,660
I'll hurry it up.

290
00:16:33,740 --> 00:16:34,860
The approval of the detachment

291
00:16:34,860 --> 00:16:36,020
needs to be processed.

292
00:16:36,490 --> 00:16:37,700
Give me some more time,

293
00:16:37,940 --> 00:16:38,740
Okay?

294
00:16:40,990 --> 00:16:41,790
Bye.

295
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:54,190
[Fire]

296
00:17:01,780 --> 00:17:02,860
Are you hiding something from me?

297
00:17:03,540 --> 00:17:04,980
